      <section eId="sec_249_A">
        <num>249-A</num>
        <heading>Waiver of counsel</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_249_A__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>the minor\nunderstands the nature of the charges, the possible dispositional\nalternatives and the possible defenses to the charges,</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_249_A__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>the minor\npossesses the maturity, knowledge and intelligence necessary to conduct\nhis or her own defense, and</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_249_A__subsec_c">
          <num>(c)</num>
          <content>
            <p>waiver is in the best interest of the\nminor.\n  * NB Effective until September 1, 2030\n  * ยง 249-a. Waiver of counsel. A minor who is a subject of a juvenile\ndelinquency or person in need of supervision proceeding shall be\npresumed to lack the requisite knowledge and maturity to waive the\nappointment of an attorney. This presumption may be rebutted only after\nan attorney has been appointed and the court determines after a hearing\nat which the attorney appears and participates and upon clear and\nconvincing evidence that</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_249_A__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>the minor understands the nature of the\ncharges, the possible dispositional alternatives and the possible\ndefenses to the charges,</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_249_A__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>the minor possesses the maturity, knowledge\nand intelligence necessary to conduct his or her own defense, and</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_249_A__subsec_c">
          <num>(c)</num>
          <content>
            <p>\nwaiver is in the best interest of the minor.\n  * NB Effective September 1, 2030\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
